args:
Finlorda confesses that he manipulated Notte's
memories and her meeting with the prince in
order to observe him. He then reveals that
the prince was created using faerie magic and
a piece of the Other's flesh.
You were not originally to live in South\nGrastaea, but here in the Faerie Kingdom.
You were to live in the land of your birth.
Wait, wait, wait. Back the heck up.\nTHIS is where I was born?!
But I always thought Notte was born\nback in South Grastaea.
Yeah, I've never even been OUT of\nSouth Grastaea until just right now!
The reason you do not recall anything\nof this kingdom is because of me.
I sealed away and replaced all memories\nof your time in the Faerie Kingdom.
Since ancient times, we faeries have\nproduced all manner of magics.
Among those is a particular spell which\ncan be used to manipulate the memories\nof a living creature.
I utilized a portion of this magic when I\ninformed Notte of the mountain path\nthat led you to this manor.

This same spell is also how I sealed away
Notte's memories and replaced them
with false ones of having grown up in
South Grastaea.
I put you to sleep, ordered you brought\nto South Grastaea, and then...
I awakened you in the palace\nof Sol Alberia.
But that means that when Zethia and I\nfirst met Notte, it was...
Planned, yesâ€”though I did my best\nto ensure it seemed spontaneous.
So I didn't just run into Zethia by chance\nback in the day? It was, like, a scheme?
Then I met {player_name} and\nwe all became pals and...
If I might interject? Supposing your tale is\ntrue, I still fail to understand the reason.

You took Notte from the Faerie Kingdom
and awakened her in front of the palace...
why? To what end would you possibly go
to so much bother and difficulty?
I needed to use Notte in order to watch\nover {player_name}.
If you continue speaking in riddles,\nI am going to be VERY upset.
Even among faeries, Notte is particularly\nblessed with the power of mana, so I\nfound a way to harness it for my own ends.
Using this mana, I caused her memories\nand perceptions to flow back to me.
Thus, I could remain here in the Faerie\nKingdom while still keeping track of\n{player_name}'s activities.
You've been spying on my whole LIFE?!
No. No, no no... This is not happening...
How could you do such a thing?
Yeah, she's our friend, not some kinda\ncreepy spy tool for you to throw around!
You are lower than low to use her so.
I took these actions of my own free will,\nand seek neither excuse nor penance.
Well good, 'cause we ain't about to forgive\nya for messin' with Notte's life!
The unjustness of your actions\nstaggers the imagination!
For the love of everything good and holy,\nwould all of you PLEASE shut up?!

If you ever want to learn WHY he did the
things he did, you need to stop yelling
about how shocked you are and simply
LISTEN to the man!
Right then. Continue, if you please.
Tell us why you went to such lengths\nto observe {player_name}.

And while you're at it, you can explain how
it relates to the secret agreement you
made with my father that saw Nedrick
and {player_name} exchanged.
The truth, sir, and quickly.\nMy patience is also at its end.
I needed to keep a constant eye on him\nin the unlikely event that anything\nabnormal happened to his body.
Why did you think something abnormal\nmight happen with my body?
Yours is not a natural-born life.
You were created through a combination\nof faerie magic and a thing...inhuman.
Yesâ€”and the thing that became your body\nwas something from a great struggle\nin ages long since past...
You were created with a piece\nof the Other's flesh.
